image:image.image:title: An image showing a dozen of Barbie dolls, each wearing very different clothings. This image reflects Billie Eilish's ideology. It is also a resistance and rejection to a single, unrealistic standard for women.
A photo of a Barbie doll, connecting to the Barbie movie. Her perfect smile and blurry background hints a sense of uncertainty and complexity
An image of a phone playing Billie Eilish's song.

An image of a Barbie but with an affect that shows multiple reflections of her. This connects both to the Barbie movie and the struggle implied in the song, where one tries to find oneself. The multiple reflection presents a sense of disorientation that needs to be sort out. It also cushions for Billie Eilish's production idea in her MV.

An image of Billie Eilish standing on stage and performing. She stands in the higher position and center of the photo, creating a sense of determination and ease. Even though she seems alone, she is in path becoming who she wants to be.
An image of a girl looking in the mirror. It reflects the part in the text where one looks in the mirror and starts to wonder about one's imperfections.
An image of a lonely and sad girl. This represents the feeling of uncertainty and struggle at the start of the journey, noticing that she is not fully sure of her value and identity.

An image of Billie Eilish's eye, which is a very determined look. This is like the end journey of self-discovery. It does mean full understanding, but it means embracing oneself and finding the firm resolution.
